parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle fails to stop or slows down unexpectedly
the ABS and brake warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
difficulty shifting gears
the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
the vehicle loses power
difficulty restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the ABS and brake warning lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

the clutch pedal sticks to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the accelerator pedal to stick, resulting in loss of vehicle control, increased risk of accidents, and potential injury or death.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks
the vehicle accelerates unintentionally
the vehicle stalls or dies
the engine RPMs fluctuate
and the vehicle may jerk or lurch forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking accelerator pedal can cause loss of vehicle control, increased risk of accidents, and potential injury or death.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks
the vehicle accelerates unintentionally
the vehicle stalls or dies
the engine RPMs fluctuate
and the vehicle may jerk or lurch forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning cruise control can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control suddenly gives the vehicle a burst of speed
the vehicle accelerates unintentionally

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Shock Tower/Rear Subframe Corrosion Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the rear shock tower or rear subframe can cause the shock absorber to detach from the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: Loud banging or clunking noise from the rear of the vehicle
rust visible on the rear wheel wells
shock absorber detaching from the vehicle
and uneven ride.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Master Cylinder/Concentric Slave Cylinder Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder or concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
